<i>æsc</i> ‘ash tree’."],"variants":[{"name":"Alston","meanings":["English and Scottish:","from the Middle English personal name <i>Alstan</i>, which is a coalescence of several different Old English personal names: <i>Æthelstān</i> ‘noble stone’, <i>Ælfstān</i> ‘elf stone’, <i>Ealdstān</i> ‘old stone’, or <i>Ealhstān</i> ‘temple stone’.","habitational name from any of various places called Alston (in Cumbria, Lancashire, Devon, and Somerset) or Alstone (in Gloucestershire and Staffordshire). With the exception of Alston in Cumbria, which is formed with the Old Norse personal name <i>Halfdan</i>, these placenames all consist of an Old English personal name + Old English <i>tūn</i> ‘settlement’, for example <i>Ælfsige</i> in the case of Alstone in Gloucestershire."]}]},{"name":"Steeple","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["1  English: locative name from Steeple Grange in Wirksworth (Derbys) ‘steep hill’, recorded as  <i>Stephul(l)</i> about 1230 and  <i>Steple</i> in 1363.","2  English: locative name occasionally from Middle English  <i>stepel</i>,  <i>steple</i> ‘tower, steeple; steep place’ (Old English  <i>stepel</i>), and given to someone who lived by a tower or a steep place, or who came from a place so named, such as Steeple Court in Botley (Hants) and Steeple (Dorset, Essex)."],"variants":[{"name":"Steeples","meanings":["English (Derbyshire): variant of <b>Steeple</b>, with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>. <i>Steeple</i> may either be a habitational name from Steeple Grange in Wirksworth (Derbyshire), from Old English <i>stēap</i> ‘steep’ + <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’, or else arise from Middle English <i>stepel</i>, <i>steple</i> ‘steep place; tower, steeple’ (Old English <i>stȳpel</i>, <i>stīepel</i>, <i>stēpel</i>), used as a topographic name for someone who lived at a steep place or by a tower, or a habitational name for someone who came from a place so named, such as Steeple (Dorset), Steeple Court in Botley (Hampshire), Steephill in Ventnor (Isle of Wight), and Steeple (Essex)."]},{"name":"Staple","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>stapel</i> ‘post’ (Old English <i>stapol</i>), used either as a topographic name for someone who lived near a boundary post, or a habitational name from a place so named, such as Staple Fitzpaine (Somerset) or Staple (Kent).","English: in North Lancashire, a variant of   Stable  .","Americanized form of German   Stapel  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Steeple Aston was born before 1300, in England, United Kingdom. She married Thomas Abberbury. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. She died after 1353."},"et":{"Bef 1300–after 1353":"enne 1300–pärast 1353","1308–1346":"1308–1346","1291–1337":"1291–1337","1318–Female":"1318–Surnud","1327–1420":"1327–1420","1300–1353":"1300–1353","Aft 1346":"pärast 1346","1291":"1291","1327":"1327","1337":"1337","1346":"1346","Bef 1300":"enne 1300","about 1327":"umbes 1327","1300":"1300","1420":"1420","1353":"1353","after 1353":"pärast 1353","1308":"1308","1318":"1318","Alberbury, Shropshire, England":"Alberbury, Shropshire, England","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Adderbury, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Adderbury, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Bef 1300–after 1353":"ennen vuotta 1300–1353 jälkeen","1308–1346":"1308–1346","1291–1337":"1291–1337","1318–Female":"1318–Kuollut","1327–1420":"1327–1420","1300–1353":"1300–1353","Aft 1346":"1346 jälkeen","1291":"1291","1327":"1327","1337":"1337","1346":"1346","Bef 1300":"ennen vuotta 1300","about 1327":"noin 1327","1300":"1300","1420":"1420","1353":"1353","after 1353":"1353 jälkeen","1308":"1308","1318":"1318","Alberbury, Shropshire, England":"Alberbury, Shropshire, England","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Adderbury, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom"